a '''Wayside Pulpit''' is a roadside sign fronting churches and other religious worship centers, whose message is changed regularly, often weekly, and is typically welcoming or scriptural, [[[philosophy|philosophical]], spiritual, or otherwise uplifting quotations.

Among denominations, [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unitarian_Universalist Unitarian Universalists] are the ones who most commonly use the term for their message marquees.   The [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unitarian_Universalist_Association Unitarian Universalist Association] has provided 
congregations and communities spiritual refreshment in the form 
of the [http://www.uua.org/worshipweb/wayside/index.html Wayside Community Pulpit] for four decades.